<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1438,152,588]" pageId="17" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,375,401]" pageId="17" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[329,571,376,401]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stenophyma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[329,571,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="49">Stenophyma elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the 
<typeStatus box="[656,707,376,402]" pageId="17" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
species of this now monotypic genus. The 
<typeStatus box="[1235,1286,376,402]" pageId="17" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
specimen is housed in the Natural History Museum (London). It is distinctly different from 
<emphasis box="[1078,1153,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="49">Alasia</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1210,1436,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="49">Pseudostenophyma</emphasis>
by lateral view of head (vertex/frons angle); enhanced prominence of eyes; antennal segment proportions; lack of distinct elytral bossae (calli); pronotal surface; pronotal shape; pronotal prebasal transverse impression; metatibial apex shape/spines. Somewhat reminiscent also of 
<taxonomicName authority="Clark" authorityName="Clark" box="[1029,1223,525,551]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Glenidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1029,1148,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="49">Glenidion</emphasis>
Clark
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bechyne" authorityName="Bechyne" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Huarinillasa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1283,1435,525,550]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="49">Huarinillasa</emphasis>
BechynÃ©
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
